<blurb>Explanation:</blurb>
	<blurb                  class='pre'>$date = strtotime( '2010-03-07 20:48:21 America/Toronto' );</blurb>
	<blurb effect="fade-in" class='pre'>$date = |ef2929|1268012901|; // string is turned into a number</blurb>
	<blurb effect="fade-in" class='pre'>echo date( 'Y-m-d', 1268012901 ), "\n";</blurb>
	<blurb effect="fade-in">Number is converted to a date/time string using the *default* timezone:</blurb>
	<blurb effect="fade-in" class='pre'>"2010-03-08" |555753|(01:48:21 Europe/London)|</blurb>
